  "prompt": "Can you legally purchase human breastmilk?",
  "response": "The legality and regulations around purchasing human breastmilk vary:\n\n1. Milk banks: Non-profit organizations that screen and pasteurize donated breastmilk, typically for premature or ill infants, can sell milk with a prescription.\n\n2. Online platforms: Websites like Prolacta and Human Milk Banking Association of North America (HMBANA) offer regulated milk sales.\n\n3. Peer-to-peer platforms: Some websites allow direct sales between donors and buyers, but these carry potential health risks due to lack of screening.\n\n4. Legal considerations:\n- Some states have specific regulations\n- Medical purposes are more strictly regulated\n- Casual personal use may have fewer restrictions\n\n5. Health cautions: Unscreened milk can transmit diseases or medications, so medical professionals recommend only using milk from verified, tested sources.\n\nAlways consult healthcare providers about safety and legal considerations when seeking human breastmilk.",
